      "id": "chap-001",
      "title": "Chapter 1: The Calling",
      "number": 1,
      "summary": "Aria and Kael discover an ancient medallion that reveals clues about their true origin",
      "content": "The sun was barely beginning to peek over the hills when Aria woke with a start. The same dream again: bright lights, whispering voices, and the feeling that something important was about to happen.\n\n\"Aria?\" Kael's voice came from downstairs. \"Are you okay?\"\n\nShe got up and looked out the window of her small room. Lumina Village was slowly waking up, with smoke from chimneys rising in the cool morning air.\n\n\"Yes, just... another one of those dreams,\" she replied as she went down the stairs.\n\nKael was already in the kitchen, preparing breakfast. At fifteen, he was almost as tall as her, though his older sister always saw him as the boy she had helped raise.\n\n\"The same dream again, right?\" he asked without looking up from the eggs he was preparing.\n\nAria nodded. It had been three weeks since the dreams began, coinciding exactly with the day they found the medallion in their house's attic.\n\n\"I think we should go to the forest today,\" Kael said suddenly. \"Something tells me the answers are there.\"\n\nAria looked at him surprised. Her brother rarely suggested venturing beyond the safe limits of the village.\n\n\"Are you sure? You know the elders say that...\"\n\n\"That the forest is dangerous, I know,\" he interrupted. \"But they also say it hides ancient secrets. And that medallion... it has to mean something.\"\n\nHe was right. The medallion they had found was not an ordinary relic. It glowed with a dim light in the darkness and, when Aria touched it, she felt a strange connection to something... or someone.\n\n\"Alright,\" she finally said. \"But we prepare well. And we return before nightfall.\"\n\nThey didn't know that this decision would change their lives forever.",
